sequenceDiagram
    participant C as 🖥 Client
    participant S as ⚙️ Service
    participant DB as 🗄 Idempotency Store

    Note over C,DB: ✅ First request — token unseen
    C->>S: POST /orders {clientToken: "tok-abc", ...}
    S->>DB: Lookup "tok-abc"
    DB-->>S: Not found
    S->>S: Execute → create order
    S->>DB: Store "tok-abc" → {orderId, response, expires: now+8h}
    S-->>C: 201 Created {orderId: "ord-xyz"}

    Note over C,DB: ✅ Network failure — safe retry
    C->>S: POST /orders {clientToken: "tok-abc", ...}
    S->>DB: Lookup "tok-abc"
    DB-->>S: Found → replay response
    S-->>C: 201 Created {orderId: "ord-xyz"} — no new order created

    Note over C,DB: ⛔ Same token, different params — conflict
    C->>S: POST /orders {clientToken: "tok-abc", quantity: 99}
    S->>DB: Lookup "tok-abc"
    DB-->>S: Found — params differ
    S-->>C: 409 Conflict {conflictingOrderId: "ord-xyz"}

    Note over C,DB: ♻️ Token retention window
    S->>DB: Purge tokens older than min(8h, resource-lifetime + 1h)
